3	9	BRD-REQ-1104-v0.2	0.2	Final	{"meta": {"title": "TC_BRD_BANK_LOAN_004", "doc_id": "BRD-REQ-1104-v0.2", "status": "Draft", "version": "0.2", "category": "Other", "priority": "High", "ai_models": ["Azure OpenAI gpt-4o-mini (classification + generation)"], "request_id": 9, "generated_at": "2026-04-20T05:54:56.190Z", "effective_date": "20 April 2026", "request_number": "REQ-1104", "source_messages": 14, "enhanced_from_version": "0.1", "enhancement_comment_count": 1}, "sections": {"scope": {"title": "Scope", "number": "3", "summary": "This initiative delivers an end-to-end other processing capability for \\"TC_BRD_BANK_LOAN_004\\". The system scope encompasses 7 core functional areas, spanning document upload & bank statement ingestion through to automated notifications & stakeholder communication. All items listed below constitute the Phase 1 delivery scope. Capabilities noted as out-of-scope are explicitly excluded and must not be included in the Phase 1 build or testing.", "in_scope": ["Document Upload & Bank Statement Ingestion", "Third-Party Data Parsing & API Integration", "Financial Data Extraction & Income Assessment Engine", "Risk Assessment & Fraud Detection", "Customer Consent Capture & Regulatory Compliance", "Automated Case Routing & Manual Underwriting Workflow", "Automated Notifications & Stakeholder Communication"], "out_of_scope": ["Later we can support net banking fetch", "Later we can support net banking fetch"], "process_flow": [{"step": 1, "actor": "Customer", "action": "Reviews the data access and processing consent notice and grants explicit approval", "outcome": "Consent record created with timestamp and session attribution; processing unlocked"}, {"step": 2, "actor": "Customer", "action": "Uploads bank statement(s) via the portal interface", "outcome": "Document validated; unique reference ID generated; parsing workflow triggered"}, {"step": 3, "actor": "System", "action": "Validates uploaded document for file type, size constraints, and structural integrity", "outcome": "Document accepted or rejected with a descriptive error message returned to the customer"}, {"step": 4, "actor": "System", "action": "Submits validated document to the configured third-party parsing API via secure, authenticated REST call", "outcome": "Structured transaction JSON received ΓÇö salary credits, EMIs, balances, and bounce events categorised"}, {"step": 5, "actor": "System", "action": "Executes the income assessment engine: identifies salary credits, calculates 6-month average income, aggregates EMI obligations, counts bounce events", "outcome": "Financial summary record created and stored; assessment status set"}, {"step": 6, "actor": "System", "action": "Applies fraud detection rules and risk scoring to the extracted transaction data", "outcome": "Risk flags attached to case record; high-risk cases marked for escalation"}, {"step": 7, "actor": "System", "action": "Routes the case based on assessment outcome: eligible cases progress automatically; insufficient or flagged cases are directed to the manual underwriting queue", "outcome": "Case status updated; underwriter assigned and notified if manual review is required"}, {"step": 8, "actor": "System", "action": "Dispatches automated notification to the customer and relevant internal stakeholders with the assessment outcome", "outcome": "Notification delivered within SLA; delivery confirmed and logged"}, {"step": 9, "actor": "System", "action": "Writes a complete, immutable audit log entry recording all actors, decisions, API interactions, and timestamps for this processing cycle", "outcome": "Compliance record created; audit trail closed for this case"}]}, "appendix": {"title": "Appendix A: Key Conversation Excerpts", "keywords": ["statement", "bank", "customer", "salary", "income", "api", "yes", "upload", "last", "months", "pdf", "average"], "messages": [{"text": "Yes, customer should upload last 6 months bank statement in PDF format.", "sender": "Arun", "marked_at": "2026-04-08T14:26:16.708Z"}, {"text": "What information should be extracted from bank statement?\\n", "sender": "BA 1", "marked_at": "2026-04-08T14:26:18.877Z"}, {"text": "We can integrate with Account Aggregator or third party statement parsing API", "sender": "itmanager", "marked_at": "2026-04-08T14:26:20.070Z"}, {"text": "Yes, average salary credit for last 6 months should be calculated.\\n", "sender": "Arun", "marked_at": "2026-04-08T14:26:23.582Z"}, {"text": "Also flag irregular income patterns like sudden drop in salary or inconsistent credits", "sender": "Arun", "marked_at": "2026-04-08T14:26:24.696Z"}, {"text": "Need detection of suspicious transactions like high cash deposits before loan application", "sender": "Arun", "marked_at": "2026-04-08T14:26:26.056Z"}, {"text": "What file formats should be supported?", "sender": "BA 1", "marked_at": "2026-04-08T14:26:27.742Z"}, {"text": "PDF initially. Later we can support net banking fetch.", "sender": "Arun", "marked_at": "2026-04-08T14:26:30.407Z"}, {"text": "If salary not detected, case should go for manual review", "sender": "Arun", "marked_at": "2026-04-08T14:26:31.125Z"}, {"text": "Customer consent required before fetching bank statement data.", "sender": "Arun", "marked_at": "2026-04-08T14:26:31.997Z"}, {"text": "API response time expected 8ΓÇô10 seconds.", "sender": "Arun", "marked_at": "2026-04-08T14:26:33.380Z"}, {"text": "Do we want customer to upload bank statement during loan application?\\n", "sender": "BA 1", "marked_at": "2026-04-09T13:44:00.293Z"}, {"text": "Should we calculate average monthly income?\\n", "sender": "BA 1", "marked_at": "2026-04-14T23:03:26.131Z"}, {"text": "Currently income verification is manual. Operations team checks bank statements manually which\\ntakes 1ΓÇô2 days. We want automated assessment of income using bank statement analysis API.", "sender": "arunnayaka99@gmail.com", "marked_at": "2026-04-20T00:14:26.113Z"}]}, "objective": {"text": "Objective: By the end of Q4 2024, increase the approval rate of bank loan applications by 15% through the implementation of an enhanced credit assessment algorithm, thereby improving customer satisfaction and reducing processing time. This initiative aims to streamline the loan approval process, ultimately resulting in a projected increase of $2 million in loan disbursements within the same period.", "goals": ["Deliver an end-to-end, automated other processing workflow from document upload & bank statement ingestion to automated notifications & stakeholder communication", "Eliminate manual data extraction effort through automated income assessment and risk scoring, with configurable rules maintained by the business team", "Establish reliable, SLA-governed third-party API integration for real-time bank statement data enrichment", "Achieve full regulatory compliance ΓÇö including customer consent capture and data minimisation ΓÇö from the first production release", "Maintain complete, immutable audit traceability for every processing decision to support regulatory review and internal governance requirements"], "title": "Business Objective & Goals", "number": "2"}, "action_items": {"items": [], "title": "Action Items & Next Steps", "number": "10"}, "stakeholders": {"list": [{"name": "Arun", "role": "Primary Stakeholder / Business Owner"}, {"name": "BA 1", "role": "Discussion Participant"}, {"name": "itmanager", "role": "Discussion Participant"}, {"name": "arunnayaka99@gmail.com", "role": "Discussion Participant"}, {"name": "Business Analyst", "role": "BRD Author / Requirements Owner"}, {"name": "IT Implementation", "role": "Technical Feasibility & Implementation"}], "title": "Stakeholder Analysis", "number": "4"}, "brd_readiness": {"score": 3, "title": "BRD Readiness Assessment", "checks": [{"pass": true, "label": "Requirements defined"}, {"pass": true, "label": "Stakeholders identified"}, {"pass": true, "label": "Timelines mentioned"}, {"pass": false, "label": "Success criteria present"}, {"pass": false, "label": "Risks / concerns raised"}], "number": "11", "readinessLevel": "Medium ΓÇö a few gaps remain"}, "risk_register": {"items": [], "title": "Risk Register", "number": "9"}, "business_rules": {"items": [{"id": "BR-001", "description": "A minimum of 6 months of bank statement history is required for income assessment. Submissions with fewer than 6 months of data shall be flagged for manual review."}, {"id": "BR-002", "description": "Average monthly income shall be computed from identified salary credits over the most recent 6-month period. Months with no salary credit shall be treated as zero and included in the average calculation."}, {"id": "BR-003", "description": "Applications where automated salary identification yields no result shall be automatically routed to the manual underwriting queue. The routing decision shall be logged with the triggering reason."}, {"id": "BR-004", "description": "Irregular income patterns ΓÇö including salary drops exceeding 30% month-on-month or more than 2 months of absent credit ΓÇö shall be flagged as a risk indicator and attached to the case record."}, {"id": "BR-005", "description": "High-value cash deposits occurring within 90 days of loan application shall be automatically flagged for fraud review. The flagging threshold shall be configurable by the risk team."}, {"id": "BR-006", "description": "Customer explicit consent must be captured and stored before any bank statement data is fetched or processed. Processing initiated without a valid consent record is prohibited."}, {"id": "BR-007", "description": "Third-party API integrations shall complete within the agreed response time SLA. Calls exceeding the timeout threshold shall trigger a configurable fallback response and generate an operational alert."}, {"id": "BR-008", "description": "PDF is the supported bank statement format for Phase 1. Net banking fetch and direct aggregator access are deferred to Phase 2 and must not be included in the Phase 1 delivery scope."}, {"id": "BR-009", "description": "All state-changing operations shall be recorded in an immutable audit log capturing actor identity, action, affected entity, input parameters, and outcome timestamp."}, {"id": "BR-010", "description": "All business logic and data validation shall be enforced server-side. Client-side validation is supplementary and must not be relied upon as the sole control."}], "title": "Business Rules", "number": "7"}, "executive_summary": {"text": "The \\"TC_BRD_BANK_LOAN_004\\" project aims to enhance the accuracy of customer eligibility assessments for bank loans by leveraging comprehensive salary and income data, thereby addressing existing inefficiencies and improving customer satisfaction. The proposed solution involves the development of a streamlined assessment system that integrates advanced data analytics to ensure precise evaluations. By implementing this solution, the organization will not only reduce processing times but also foster greater trust and loyalty among customers.", "title": "Executive Summary", "number": "1"}, "functional_requirements": {"items": [{"id": "FR-001", "title": "Document Upload & Bank Statement Ingestion", "source": "Key Stakeholder Discussion", "priority": "Must Have", "rationale": "Bank statement ingestion is the foundational step upon which all downstream income assessment and risk analysis depends. A reliable, secure upload mechanism is a prerequisite for every other functional capability in this initiative.", "description": "The system shall provide a secure, customer-facing document upload interface that accepts bank statements in PDF and Net Banking Fetch format. Uploaded documents shall be validated for file type compliance, maximum file size, and structural integrity prior to acceptance. Each successful upload shall generate a unique document reference identifier and trigger the automated parsing workflow. Upload progress shall be communicated to the customer in real time. Validation failures shall be surfaced with clear, actionable error messages. The raw document shall be discarded from storage immediately after extraction is complete, in line with data minimisation requirements."}, {"id": "FR-002", "title": "Third-Party Data Parsing & API Integration", "source": "Key Stakeholder Discussion", "priority": "Must Have", "rationale": "The parsing API is the primary data enrichment engine. Its reliability, response quality, and error handling directly determine the accuracy of the income assessment output.", "description": "The system shall integrate with We can integrate with account aggregator or third party statement parsing api to extract structured transaction data from submitted bank statement documents. The integration shall be implemented as a secure, authenticated outbound REST API call. The API shall return a structured JSON payload containing categorised transaction records within 8ΓÇô10 second. The system shall implement configurable timeout handling: calls exceeding the SLA threshold shall trigger a fallback response and generate an operational alert. API credentials shall be stored as environment-scoped secrets and must not be embedded in source code or logs."}, {"id": "FR-003", "title": "Financial Data Extraction & Income Assessment Engine", "source": "Key Stakeholder Discussion", "priority": "Must Have", "rationale": "Accurate and standardised income assessment is the core business objective of this initiative. The calculation methodology must be consistent, configurable, auditable, and aligned with the organisation's credit policy to ensure sound lending decisions.", "description": "The system shall execute an automated income assessment engine against the extracted transaction data. The engine shall: (a) identify salary credit narrations across supported bank formats using a configurable, maintainable pattern-matching library; (b) compute the applicant's average monthly income from salary credits over the most recent six-month period; (c) aggregate all existing EMI obligations identified in the transaction history to derive the net repayment capacity; (d) count cheque and NEFT return (bounce) incidents as a credit risk signal. The resulting financial summary ΓÇö comprising average income, EMI total, bounce count, and assessment status ΓÇö shall be stored as a structured record and used as the primary input for the eligibility determination workflow."}, {"id": "FR-004", "title": "Risk Assessment & Fraud Detection", "source": "Key Stakeholder Discussion", "priority": "Must Have", "rationale": "Fraud detection protects the organisation from credit risk and financial loss. Automated flagging ensures that high-risk applications receive appropriate scrutiny without creating operational bottlenecks for clean cases.", "description": "The system shall apply a configurable ruleset of fraud detection and risk indicators to the extracted transaction data. Suspicious signals ΓÇö including high-value cash deposits within 90 days of application, sudden income drops exceeding defined thresholds, absent or highly irregular salary credits, and elevated bounce counts ΓÇö shall be identified and attached to the case record as structured risk flags. Cases exceeding configurable risk score thresholds shall be automatically escalated to the risk review queue. All fraud detection rule configurations shall be manageable by authorised risk personnel without requiring a code deployment."}, {"id": "FR-005", "title": "Customer Consent Capture & Regulatory Compliance", "source": "Key Stakeholder Discussion", "priority": "Must Have", "rationale": "Explicit consent is a regulatory obligation under applicable data protection law. Failure to obtain and evidence consent exposes the organisation to regulatory enforcement action and reputational risk.", "description": "The system shall obtain and record explicit, informed customer consent before initiating any bank data fetch or document processing. The consent capture interface shall clearly describe: the data to be accessed, the purpose of processing, the third parties involved, and the data retention policy. Consent records shall be timestamped, attributed to the authenticated customer session, and stored in an immutable log. Processing must not proceed ΓÇö and the system must prevent API calls from being made ΓÇö in the absence of a valid, recorded consent event. The consent framework shall be reviewed and approved by the legal/compliance team before implementation."}, {"id": "FR-006", "title": "Automated Case Routing & Manual Underwriting Workflow", "source": "Key Stakeholder Discussion", "priority": "Must Have", "rationale": "Not all applications can be assessed automatically. A defined fallback routing mechanism ensures that edge cases and high-risk applications receive appropriate human review without creating operational ambiguity.", "description": "The system shall implement an automated case routing engine that directs each completed income assessment to the appropriate outcome path. Cases meeting all defined eligibility criteria shall be marked for automated progression. Cases where salary income cannot be reliably identified, where fraud risk indicators are flagged, or where data quality is insufficient shall be automatically routed to the manual underwriting queue with a structured case summary. The manual review interface shall present the assigned underwriter with all extracted financial data, risk flags, and a structured decision capture form. Routing decisions and manual overrides shall be fully logged for audit purposes."}, {"id": "FR-007", "title": "Automated Notifications & Stakeholder Communication", "source": "Domain Signal (best practice inclusion)", "priority": "Must Have", "rationale": "Timely, accurate communication maintains customer confidence and operational transparency. Automated notifications reduce manual follow-up effort and create a consistent, auditable communication trail.", "description": "The system shall dispatch automated notifications to relevant parties at defined process milestones, including: document receipt confirmation, processing completion, assessment outcome (approved / referred / declined), and manual review routing. Notifications shall be delivered via the configured channel (email, SMS, or portal message) within a defined SLA. Failed notification attempts shall be retried up to three times before an operational alert is raised. Notification templates shall be configurable by authorised administrators without requiring a code change."}, {"id": "FR-008", "title": "The system shall provide a clear and concise", "source": "Stakeholder Feedback (v0.2)", "priority": "Must Have", "rationale": "", "description": "The system shall provide a clear and concise articulation of the business objectives and goals."}, {"id": "FR-009", "title": "The system shall include a mechanism for stakeholders", "source": "Stakeholder Feedback (v0.2)", "priority": "Must Have", "rationale": "", "description": "The system shall include a mechanism for stakeholders to review and provide feedback on business objectives and goals."}, {"id": "FR-010", "title": "The system shall ensure that business objectives and", "source": "Stakeholder Feedback (v0.2)", "priority": "Must Have", "rationale": "", "description": "The system shall ensure that business objectives and goals are easily accessible and understandable to all stakeholders."}], "title": "Functional Requirements", "number": "5"}, "integration_requirements": {"items": [{"id": "INT-001", "sla": "Response within 8ΓÇô10 second", "auth": "Secure API Key", "type": "REST API", "input": "PDF / Net Banking Fetch", "output": "JSON ΓÇö structured transaction data", "system": "We can integrate with account aggregator or third party statement parsing api", "direction": "Outbound", "description": "Outbound REST integration with We can integrate with account aggregator or third party statement parsing api to extract structured transaction data from submitted bank statement documents. The API shall return a categorised JSON payload including salary credits, EMI transactions, bounce events, and summary balances."}, {"id": "INT-002", "sla": "Response within 8ΓÇô10 second", "auth": "Secure API Key", "type": "REST API", "input": "PDF / Net Banking Fetch", "output": "JSON Structured Data", "system": "We want automated assessment of income using bank statement analysis api", "direction": "Outbound", "description": "Fallback integration with We want automated assessment of income using bank statement analysis api as an alternate statement parsing provider in the event the primary vendor is unavailable or returns an error response."}, {"id": "INT-003", "sla": "Upload acknowledgement < 5 s; processing completion < 30 s", "auth": "JWT Bearer Token (authenticated customer session)", "type": "File Upload", "input": "PDF document (maximum file size per policy)", "output": "Document reference ID + parsed transaction JSON", "system": "Document Upload & Temporary Storage Service", "direction": "Inbound", "description": "Customer-facing inbound file upload endpoint that accepts PDF bank statements, validates file type and size, stores the document temporarily during processing, and discards the raw file after data extraction is complete."}], "title": "Integration Requirements", "number": "8"}, "non_functional_requirements": {"items": [{"id": "NFR-001", "category": "Performance", "description": "System response times shall meet agreed SLA targets. API calls shall complete within the specified time window. UI interactions shall respond within 2 seconds under normal load."}, {"id": "NFR-002", "category": "Security", "description": "All data access shall require authentication. Sensitive financial and personal data shall be encrypted in transit (TLS 1.2+) and at rest. Role-based access controls shall restrict functionality to authorised users only."}, {"id": "NFR-003", "category": "Compliance & Audit", "description": "All state-changing operations and data access events shall be logged in an immutable audit trail. Logs shall be retained per the organisation's data governance policy and made available to authorised compliance personnel on request."}, {"id": "NFR-004", "category": "Regulatory Compliance & Consent", "description": "Explicit, informed customer consent shall be obtained and recorded before any personal or financial data is fetched, processed, or shared. Consent records shall be stored with timestamp and session attribution for regulatory audit."}, {"id": "NFR-005", "category": "Data Storage & Privacy", "description": "Only derived financial summary values shall be persisted after processing. Raw bank statements and full transaction data shall not be stored beyond the immediate processing session. Storage minimisation is required to meet data protection obligations."}, {"id": "NFR-006", "category": "Interoperability", "description": "The system shall expose documented REST APIs and conform to agreed integration contracts with third-party vendors. API versioning shall be maintained to avoid breaking changes."}], "title": "Non-Functional Requirements", "number": "6"}}}	3	2026-04-20 05:55:02.273082	2026-04-20 05:58:51.501405
